        "curveballHtml": "You've just sent your negotiation plan to your VP Sales. She calls you immediately: <em>\"Good plan, but we're 3 weeks out from quarter close. This feels too slow. I need a clean forecast commit by Friday. If we have to go to the floor (16% discount) to close this week, let's do it. What's your forecast commit for Weststahl?\"</em><br><br>The internal floor is €2.7M (16% discount). Your current plan involves more strategic engagement.",
        "recapText": "My plan: Re-engage Dr. Marten to apply internal pressure, then address Ms. Eichler's price and terms by offering a modest discount (e.g., 10%) in exchange for a 3-year term and faster payment. For the exit clause, I'll propose a review after year 2, not year 1.",
