        "curveballHtml": "It's Saturday morning. The day-ahead auction just closed. Your recommended actions were partially implemented. Then, the grid operator (TSO) calls: a major transmission line unexpectedly tripped offline in Southern Germany. To prevent a cascade, they're issuing a <strong>mandatory curtailment order for 1.5 GW of solar generation</strong> across the region, effective 10:00-14:00 Sunday. Our solar assets are in that region.<br><br>The Head of Trading texts: <em>\"TSO just called. How does this impact our Sunday plan? We need to react fast.\"</em>",
        "recapText": "My primary recommendation for Sunday is to optimize our storage assets and shut down Sögelheim coal. We should charge our 80 MWh pump-storage and 40 MWh battery during negative price hours (10-14) and discharge during the evening peak (18-22). This mitigates losses from our wind PPA and solar exposure while capitalizing on price spreads. The main risk is the evening ramp-up being steeper than forecast, so we must monitor intraday prices closely.",
